<!-- // Written by EpiTech Consultants

// Body below the main script -->
<style>
  div.count,
  div.report-val,
  div.num,
  div.sd {
    text-align: right;
    /* width: 65px */
  }

  tr.top-row {
    border-top: medium solid grey
  }

  table {
    font: 15px Verdana;
    width: 100%;
  }

  report-body.table,
  report-info.table {
    margin: 10px 0;
    padding: 2px 4px;
  }

  report-body.table {
    border: solid 1px #333;
  }

  report-body.td {
    width: 25%
  }

  table.th {
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  @media print {
    /* All your print styles go here */
    .hide-for-print {
      display: none !important;
    }
  }
</style>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css">
<script src="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
<script>
  var orgUnit = dhis2.report.organisationUnit
  var period = dhis2.report.periods[0]
  // Update the headers for the report
  // define the indicator groups to get. order doesn't matter now
  var ind_groups = ['YNdatZ6GQmn', 'T1qWJMe9h1w', 'zX0L6tzJUYU', 'r57O0fonc2w', 'CNyk9b3QPJv', 'jLYkCuVF5NW', 'Z1OEtTNUqJA', 'Vo5lRrgSlRg', 'f9ysMDTrLfp', 'IR5tVEnAz9L', 'Cd475p8sAl8']
  $(document).ready(function() {
    // Get the data and populate
    var uri = '../api/26/analytics.json?'
    var pd = '&dimension=pe:' + period
    var ou = '&filter=ou:' + orgUnit.id
    var extra = '&skipMeta=true&includeNumDen=true'
    // lookup each indicator group and place the data into the cells
    $.each(ind_groups, function(dim) {
      console.log("Getting Indicator Group: " + dim)
      var uri_subset = uri + "dimension=dx:IN_GROUP-" + ind_groups[dim] + pd + ou + extra
      $.get(uri_subset, function(x) {
        // hit the analytics endpoint for that indicator group
        // then run through each row and populate the values we want
        // we use includeNumDen=true since we want a count value AND the percent
        // this way it comes in one payload instead of hitting two different
        // queries
        $.each(x.rows, function(j) {
          // for each of the rows in the resulting analytics data response
          // fill in the value (percent) and the numerator (the count)
          // into the appropriately tagged spans in the body below
          suffix = {
            '-val': 2,
            '-num': 3
          }
          for (var s in suffix) {
            cell = document.getElementById(x.rows[j][0] + s)
            if (cell != null) {
              txt = x.rows[j][suffix[s]]
              // some number dressing based on how we want to display it
              if (cell.classList.contains('count')) {
                txt = parseInt(txt)
              }
              if ($(cell).hasClass('sd')) {
                txt = "(SD " + txt + ")"
              }
              if ($(cell).hasClass('pct')) {
                txt = "(" + txt + "%)"
              }
              cell.innerText = txt
            }
          }
        })
      })
    })
    var ou_name = document.getElementById('organisationUnit')
    var qtr = document.getElementById('quarter')
    var gen_dt = document.getElementById('genDate')
    // Set some properties on the header of the table
    ou_name.innerText = orgUnit.name
    qtr.innerText = period;
    gen_dt.innerText = Date();
  })

  function sort_col(col, order) {
    for (i in ind_groups) {
      sort_section(ind_groups[i], col, order)
    }
    th = document.getElementById('registry-info').getElementsByTagName('th')[col]
    th.querySelector('a').onclick = function() {
      sort_col(col, order * -1)
    }
  }

  function removed_fixed(rows) {
    // tbody =>  remove rows with 'sort-fixed' from a table
    // return an array of removed elements
    var x = []
    for (i = rows.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
      if (rows[i].classList.contains('sort-fixed')) {
        x.push(rows[i])
        rows[i].remove()
      }
    }
    return x.reverse() // since we started from the back
  }

  function sort_section(tbody_id, col, order = -1) {
    // tbody_id => the tbody tag with an id matching an indicator group
    // col => the column to sort on, 0 indexed
    // order => -1 for descending, 1 for ascending
    // text must be inside a span for this to work
    // any tr with a class attribute of 'sort-fixed' will be pulled and
    // stuck at the bottom regardless of value.
    var tbody = document.getElementById(tbody_id)
    if (tbody) {
      var first = tbody.querySelector('td').innerText
      console.log('Sorting section: ' + first)
      var first_text = first.innerText
      tbody.querySelector('td').innerText = ''
      tbody.querySelector('tr').removeAttribute('class', 'top-row')
      var fixed = removed_fixed(tbody.getElementsByTagName('tr'))
      $(tbody).find('tr').sort(function(a, b) {
        var tda = parse_val(a.cells[col].querySelector('span'))
        var tdb = parse_val(b.cells[col].querySelector('span'));
        // if a < b return 1
        return tda < tdb ? -1 * order
          // else if a > b return -1
          :
          tda > tdb ? 1 * order
          // else they are equal - return 0
          :
          0;
      }).appendTo($(tbody));
      $(tbody).append(fixed) // add the fixed rows back in
      tbody.querySelector('td').innerText = first
      // set the formatting on the top row again
      tbody.querySelector('tr').setAttribute('class', 'top-row')
    }
  }

  function parse_val(val) {
    if (isNotNull(val)) {
      if (val.classList.contains('count')) {
        var val = parseInt(val.innerText)
      } else {
        var val = val.innerText
      }
    }
    return val
  }

  function downloadCSV(csv, filename) {
    var csvFile;
    var downloadLink;
    // CSV file
    csvFile = new Blob([csv], {
      type: "text/csv"
    });
    // Download link
    downloadLink = document.createElement("a");
    // File name
    downloadLink.download = filename;
    // Create a link to the file
    downloadLink.href = window.URL.createObjectURL(csvFile);
    // Hide download link
    downloadLink.style.display = "none";
    // Add the link to DOM
    document.body.appendChild(downloadLink);
    // Click download link
    downloadLink.click();
  }

  function exportTableToCSV(filename) {
    var csv = [];
    var rows = document.querySelectorAll("table tr");
    for (var i = 0; i < rows.length; i++) {
      var row = [],

<!-- // Written by EpiTech Consultants
// 2018-03-15
// accounts@epitechconsultants.org
// aaron@epitechconsultants.org
// Body below the main script -->
<style>
div.count,div.report-val, div.num, div.sd {
  text-align: right;
  /* width: 65px */
}
tr.top-row {
  border-top: medium solid grey
}
table
{
  font:15px Verdana;
  width:100%;
}

report-body.table, report-info.table{
  margin:10px 0;
  padding:2px 4px;
}
report-body.table {
  border:solid 1px #333;

}
report-body.td {
  width: 25%
}
table.th {
  font-weight:bold;
}
@media print {
  /* All your print styles go here */
  .hide-for-print { display: none !important; }
}
</style>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css">
<script src="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

<script>
var orgUnit = dhis2.report.organisationUnit
var period = dhis2.report.periods[0]
// Update the headers for the report
// define the indicator groups to get. order doesn't matter now
var ind_groups = ['YNdatZ6GQmn', 'T1qWJMe9h1w', 'zX0L6tzJUYU', 'r57O0fonc2w', 'CNyk9b3QPJv', 'S850rdjnP5y', 'Vo5lRrgSlRg', 'f9ysMDTrLfp', 'IR5tVEnAz9L', 'Cd475p8sAl8']

$(document).ready( function() {

  // Get the data and populate

  var uri = '../api/26/analytics.json?'
  var pd = '&dimension=pe:'+period
  var ou = '&filter=ou:'+ orgUnit.id
  var extra = '&skipMeta=true&includeNumDen=true'
  // lookup each indicator group and place the data into the cells
  $.each(ind_groups, function(dim) {
    console.log("Getting Indciator Group: " + dim)
    var uri_subset = uri + "dimension=dx:IN_GROUP-" + ind_groups[dim] + pd + ou + extra
    $.get(uri_subset, function(x) {
      // hit the analytics endpoint for that indicator group
      // then run through each row and populate the values we want
      // we use includeNumDen=true since we want a count value AND the percent
      // this way it comes in one payload instead of hitting two different
      // queries
      $.each(x.rows, function(j) {
        // for each of the rows in the resulting analytics data response
        // fill in the value (percent) and the numerator (the count)
        // into the appropriately tagged spans in the body below
        suffix = {'-val':2, '-num':3}
        for (var s in suffix) {
          cell = document.getElementById(x.rows[j][0]+s)
          if (cell != null) {
            txt = x.rows[j][suffix[s]]
            // some number dressing based on how we want to display it
            if (cell.classList.contains('count')) {
              txt = parseInt(txt)
            }
            if ($(cell).hasClass('sd')) {
              txt = "(SD "+ txt +")"
            }
            if ($(cell).hasClass('pct')) {
              txt = "("+ txt +"%)"
            }
            cell.innerText = txt
          }
        }
      })
    })
  })
  var ou_name = document.getElementById('organisationUnit')
  var qtr = document.getElementById('quarter')
  var gen_dt = document.getElementById('genDate')

  // Set some properties on the header of the table
  ou_name.innerText = orgUnit.name
  qtr.innerText = period;
  gen_dt.innerText = Date();

})





function sort_col(col, order){
  for (i in ind_groups) {
    sort_section(ind_groups[i], col, order)
  }
  th = document.getElementById('registry-info').getElementsByTagName('th')[col]
  th.querySelector('a').onclick = function(){sort_col(col, order*-1)}
}

function removed_fixed(rows){
  // tbody =>  remove rows with 'sort-fixed' from a table
  // return an array of removed elements
  var x = []
  for (i =rows.length - 1; i>0;i--){
    if (rows[i].classList.contains('sort-fixed')) {
        x.push(rows[i])
        rows[i].remove()
    }
  }
  return x.reverse() // since we started from the back
}

function sort_section(tbody_id, col, order = -1){
  // tbody_id => the tbody tag with an id matching an indicator group
  // col => the column to sort on, 0 indexed
  // order => -1 for descending, 1 for ascending
  // text must be inside a span for this to work
  // any tr with a class attribute of 'sort-fixed' will be pulled and
  // stuck at the bottom regardless of value.

  var tbody = document.getElementById(tbody_id)
  if (tbody) {
    var first = tbody.querySelector('td').innerText
    console.log('Sorting section: '+ first)
    var first_text = first.innerText
    tbody.querySelector('td').innerText = ''
    tbody.querySelector('tr').removeAttribute('class', 'top-row')

    var fixed = removed_fixed(tbody.getElementsByTagName('tr'))

    $(tbody).find('tr').sort(function (a, b) {
      var tda = parse_val(a.cells[col].querySelector('span'))
      var tdb = parse_val(b.cells[col].querySelector('span'));
          // if a < b return 1
      return tda < tdb ? -1 * order
          // else if a > b return -1
            : tda > tdb ? 1 * order
           // else they are equal - return 0
             : 0;

     }).appendTo($(tbody));
    $(tbody).append(fixed) // add the fixed rows back in
    tbody.querySelector('td').innerText = first
    // set the formatting on the top row again
    tbody.querySelector('tr').setAttribute('class', 'top-row')
  }


}

function parse_val(val){
  if (isNotNull(val)) {
    if (val.classList.contains('count')) {
      var val = parseInt(val.innerText)
    }
    else {
      var val = val.innerText
    }
  }
  return val
}

function downloadCSV(csv, filename) {
  var csvFile;
  var downloadLink;
  // CSV file
  csvFile = new Blob([csv], {type: "text/csv"});
  // Download link
  downloadLink = document.createElement("a");
  // File name
  downloadLink.download = filename;
  // Create a link to the file
  downloadLink.href = window.URL.createObjectURL(csvFile);
  // Hide download link
  downloadLink.style.display = "none";
  // Add the link to DOM
  document.body.appendChild(downloadLink);
  // Click download link
  downloadLink.click();
}

function exportTableToCSV(filename) {
  var csv = [];
